summary: This is a travel authorization notification for a DOJ trip related to the Epstein investigation, specifically for witness interviews in Stockholm, Sweden from February 3-6, 2020. The authorization was approved by an unnamed approver and is pending further approval.

events.title: Planned Witness Interviews in Stockholm
events.description: DOJ travel was authorized for witness interviews in Stockholm, Sweden as part of the Epstein investigation (case reference 2018R01618).

keyFacts: A travel authorization (ID 10982121) was approved on January 28, 2020 for DOJ personnel to conduct witness interviews in Stockholm, Sweden related to the Epstein investigation.
The travel was scheduled for February 3-6, 2020 and was associated with case reference 2018R01618 and project R20NYS13341.
The authorization indicates ongoing investigative activity by the DOJ in the Epstein case as of early 2020, specifically involving international witness interviews.
The approver's name is redacted in the document, showing the use of internal DOJ travel systems (E2 Solutions) for sensitive investigations.
